Math: Set operations
For sets \(A = \{🐺, 🦊, 🐶\}\) and \(B = \{🐶, 🐷, 🐹\}\):

Set union \(A \cup B\) = {🐺, 🦊, 🐶, 🐷, 🐹}
Set intersection \(A \cap B\) = {🐶}
Set different \(A \setminus B\) = {🐺, 🦊}$, \(B \setminus A\) = {🐷, 🐹}

